\begin_layout Itemize
Keynesians - at the core of their view was the idea that governments could
 smooth out the volatility of free markets by expanding the supply of money
 and running large budget deficits when times were tough.
 The Austrians argued that recessions are necessary to compensate for unwise
 decisions made during the booms that always precede the busts.
