 governments would drive up inflation, risking major pain for the economy.
 Friedman believed that if central banks were charged with maintaining control
 of prices (using interest rates with some strict rules), most other aspects
 of the economy - unemployment, economic growth, productivity - would more
 or less take care of themselves.
\end_layout

