 Most of what people thought was money was actually credit.
 So when credit disappears, people don't have enough money.
 People are desperate for money - and central bank can print money.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Print money - this is inflationary and stimulative.
 New money is used to buy financial assets and government bonds.
 It helps to drive asset prices which makes people more creditworthy.
 However this only helps those who own financial assets.
 The central government on the other hand can buy goods and services and
